                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/16986.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Simpich</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Nogales</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-21T22:00:00-07:23">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 21, 1915—10 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your December 21. General Obregon is authorized to proceed to El Paso via
                    American Territory, provided he travels as civilian and unarmed. So inform
                    federal authorities on border, especially military authorities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
